_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"twitter","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":true},{"id":3590894,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"@bugtriage-josh \nI think their is a misunderstanding.\n\n**What I wanted to report is:**\n1.  As mentioned by you, If User A blocks User B then User A will not get any message or notification from User B, which is correct\n2. But one more thing is happening here, after blocking, User B cannot see any posts/notfication from User A, even though User A posted on User B status, which is not expected.\n3. So in this POC, attacker is using the blocked feature instead of victim\n\n**One example:**\n1. I login to twitter and block your twitter handle in my profile\n2.  I can still see your tweets and can reply on any of your tweets\n3. I open any of your tweet and reply with some spam which you would never want on your profile tweet\n4. My reply successfully posts\n5. When you open your twitter and goto that tweet, you will not see my reply. But any other twitter user will see my reply on that tweet.\n\n**What happens on other platforms:**\nIf User A blocks User B then User A must also not be allowed to post reply on User B tweets","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-11-06T01:15:01.824Z","updated_at":"2018-11-06T01:15:01.824Z","actor":{"username":"csanuragjain","cleared":true,"url":"/csanuragjain","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/058/139/bbabf05f3cf79c652d18dd0fbfe79e515798b03e_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"twitter","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3596676,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Not sure, if u received the follow up comment 